5. Cote d’Ivoire

Cote d’Ivoire has 1.2 million people and is the biggest and most populous country on the island of Africa affront, with the two other important islandic countries–Madagascar to the east and Comoros to the south –being prominently large, as well.

Credit: Wiki

Due to its location in the tropical region, food production is a very profitable business here . With an astounding 125 000 m³ of commercial agricultural land, the country has an opportunity to grow half of its food supplies at home, with the rest being produced through imports.

In the last decade, the poor economy of Côte d’Ivoire was uplifted by increased earnings from exports, online investment and new projects.
